  <prompt>
    Add a new public constant `ComposeSummarize = "compose-summarize"` to `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs` so downstream Compose code can resolve the routing entry without magic strings. This is the smallest possible additive change to the BFF AI PublicContracts surface and is the prerequisite for Phase 2 services + endpoints (021–025) and the Phase 1 `sprk_playbookconsumer` row.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer familiar with the Spaarke BFF AI PublicContracts facade (refined ADR-013, 2026-05-20). Comfortable making small additive changes to a heavily-consumed shared file.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `ConsumerTypes.ComposeSummarize` constant exists in `ConsumerTypes.cs`, the BFF builds clean, and the constant is consumable by `IConsumerRoutingService` lookups.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-09 of spec.md mandates the `ComposeSummarize` consumer-type constant. The string value `"compose-summarize"` matches the Phase 1 `sprk_playbookconsumer` row linking to Document Summary playbook id `47686eb1-9916-f111-8343-7c1e520aa4df`. This task is gated on the four Phase 0 spikes (001–004) only because the consumer-routing E2E shape (Spike #4) confirms the wire string.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Additions to PublicContracts MUST be additive constants/strings — do NOT leak AI internals (no `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService` references in this file).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">String literal MUST be `"compose-summarize"` (matches Phase 1 sprk_playbookconsumer row and Spike #4 wire shape).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">No new package references; no new DI registrations in this task.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ConsumerTypes.cs` — the canonical home for consumer-type string constants (7 active types as of 2026-06-29).</existing>
    <extension>Yes — this task EXTENDS the existing `ConsumerTypes` static class with one additional constant. No new file, no new abstraction. The task title says "add constant" not "create class."</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-09 acceptance fails — the constant does not compile, downstream Phase 2 services (021–024) cannot reference it without a magic string, and the smoke test (FR-11) cannot resolve the routing entry symbolically.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

