  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context check + load knowledge">Verify context &lt; 70%. Load spec.md FR-09, plan.md Phase 2, bff-extensions.md §A pre-merge checklist, and the existing ConsumerTypes.cs.</step>
    <step order="1" name="Inspect current ConsumerTypes surface">Read `ConsumerTypes.cs` to confirm style (const string, XML doc, ordering). Verify no existing `compose-summarize` / `ComposeSummarize` name collision.</step>
    <step order="2" name="Add constant">Add `public const string ComposeSummarize = "compose-summarize";` with an XML doc comment citing FR-09 + the Document Summary playbook id. Match existing constants' formatting.</step>
    <step order="3" name="Build BFF">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — must be clean (no warnings introduced).</step>
    <step order="4" name="Measure publish-size impact">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`; measure compressed output. Expected: ≤+0.01 MB delta vs ~45.65 MB baseline (single constant). Record in task notes.</step>
    <step order="5" name="CVE check">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — must show no new HIGH-severity CVE.</step>
    <step order="6" name="Update TASK-INDEX">Update `projects/spaarkeai-compose-r1/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 020 status to ✅. Reset `current-task.md` to next pending task.</step>
  </steps>

